{
  "stem": "24111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Left to Italy, to Hungary, to Czechoslovakia, wherever they could go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The more mobile people, I would say, started to leave.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Interesting enough, this question came up many times in my mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I can only tell you certain names are strictly Jewish, or very, very much Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Austrian, just by looking at you, could also, in many times, tell if you are Jewish or not.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think that was the beginning of the real antisemitism which was prevailing always in Austria.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I don't think--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or sit on a park bench.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I don't think so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that in the moment an directive came out and a sign was put up, the Jews were also afraid to go to a library or to cross the line and go into a movie theater when there was a-- a sign Jews were not allowed.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because at the same time, people started to get picked up and thrown into camps, because they had previous political affiliations or they were outspoken, or they had professions which the Germans didn't like, like an reporter and newscaster.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I am talking about Jewish newscasters.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I have a-- a cousin by the name of Otto Perl.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "O-T-T-O-P-E-R-L, which was, I think, four or five years older than me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in his Jews, he joined the [NON-ENGLISH] which was an-- an socialistic youth group, not because he was a communist, just because his friends were in this particular group.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the German came to Austria, all socialistic groups were immediately prosecuted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, for example, my father was a Social Democrat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the United States, there are only Republicans-- only two.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in Austria, there were many parties, and that was one of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
